comments.text: Upon my fourth watching of this video, I have come to a strange conundrum. I'm a little bit confused about Manic - in the first act, he is seen rusted so badly he cannot move, because he was sweating thinking about Mindy's boobies. She is his love desire - his goal is to be together with her. Knuckles even consoles him, and encourages him that Mindy does love Manic. But in the 3rd act, he calls her a bitch, told her her father was buying a train ticket to leave her sorry ass, then poured gasoline on her and set her on fire. I'm a little bit confused about this roundabout turn in Manic's character. Is there any explanation to this?

comments.text: The Tinman's story in the original books actually ended up having a pretty fucked up twist. He was cursed to chop off his body parts one by one, and he had them replaced with tin - all except his heart, so he decided to leave his girlfriend Nimmie Amee because he thought he couldn't love her. In a later book, he goes off in search of her and finds another tinman, the Tin Soldier, Nimmie Amee's next boyfriend who suffered the same fate but didn't worry about his missing heart, but rusted like Tinman before he could marry her. They decide to approach Nimmie together, but discover that she'd already gotten married... to a man stitched together from some of the parts of both their original bodies.
